deck: One Piece Film: Strong World Anime Comic is an anime manga based on the tenth One Piece movie, using screen captures from the film.
description:
Proper Japanese Title: ONE PIECE FILM: ストロング ワールド アニメコミックス (Wan Pīsu Sutorongu Wārudo Anime Komikkusu)

One Piece Film: Strong World Anime Comic is an anime comic that was created as a special promotional comic that uses still frames from the One Piece Film Strong World, the tenth movie in the One Piece series. The One Piece manga was created by Eiichiro Oda. This two volume anime comic is published by Shueisha's Jump Comics. Both volumes were released on December 3, 2010. One year after the film was released to theaters on December 12, 2009. The series has not been published in the U.S.
name: One Piece Film: Strong World Anime Comic

description:
A world in decline. A sky with no moon. Pandeia is a sci-fi adventure story set in Earth's distant future. The moon has long been destroyed. The world is in slow decline. Corporate city-states are in fierce competition for land, resources and developing technologies. Three such entities are in a state of cold war over a mysterious remote desert: The Cadians. It is currently occupied by clans of nomadic traders who have managed to fend off attacks and hold their ground by using the very desert against invading forces.

Enter Corben Wallace: a Theian cleric. He breaches the Northern borders with an old war sandboat and a skeleton crew, in search of a fabled temple which may hold the key to restoring balance to the Earth. Unbeknownst to him, factions from neighbouring city-states have infiltrated the Cadians intent on gaining control. Somehow, a Menoid (a piece of moon debris) has been knocked out of orbit and is spiraling towards the Cadians.

It is a race against time to gather clues, solve riddles and discover the mysterious "road to Pandeia" before the Menoid hits and hostile forces tear the desert apart.
name: Pandeia

deck: A missing video camera, the Russian Mob, and a masked vigilante come into play in THE RAPTOR, a four-part comic book mini-series by comic book creator Blair Shedd (DOCTOR WHO, DOROTHY OF OZ: PREQUEL).
description:
Journalism student Kathy Walsh and her boyfriend Paul Clemens have been found dead, their video camera missing. Realizing their own personal connection to the victims, detectives Jason Hawking and Willow Barnes of the NYPD Special Crimes Squad take the case.

As the detectives get deeper into their investigation, they discover that not only might their suspects be part of the Russian Mob, but that The Raptor may have a private stake in the case as well.
name: The Raptor

deck: Cross Manage is a shonen-sports manga created by KAITO. Due to an accident in school, Sakurai find himself blackmailed into becoming the manager for the Girl's Lacrosse team by the passionate Misora Toyoguchi.
description:
English translation of the Japanese manga Cross Manage (クロス・マネジ).

Cross Manage began as a serialized manga by Shueisha's Weekly Shōnen Jump in September 17, 2012. It's the first series from KAITO, who's both the writer and artist of the series. It was also among the series published in the digital English edition Weekly Shonen Jump, produced and translated by VIZ Media; and began same-day-digital distribution in English in January 2013.

The first volume of the series was first released by VIZ as digital only in May 14, 2013.
name: Cross Manage
